cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tree automata and state reduction techniques. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper provides an algorithm for hyper-minimization of deterministic weighted tree automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with semantics and the theory behind hyper-minimization. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with weights in tree automata, which can be seen as a form of information. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper provides implementation remarks for an efficient implementation of the algorithm.
